The paper deals with the application of the Layer-wise Relevance Propagation (LRP) algorithm to deep convolutional neural networks and Fisher Vector classifiers for image perception and prediction. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of different choices of decomposition cut-off points during the LRP-process, which is related to the optimization and learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of deep learning models for image classification and prediction also falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category, as it deals with the interpretation of neural network predictions. Finally, the paper may be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category, as it discusses the use of visualized heatmaps for image interpretation.
